The paper deals with dynamic data structures for range and nearest neighbor searching, which are fundamental problems in computational geometry and machine learning. The paper also involves geometric algorithms, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses approximate range and nearest neighbor queries, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG).
